marc21:datafield.marc21:subfield: Helen Torr Dove and Arthur Dove diary

Contains entries written by both Arthur and Helen Torr Dove (whom Arthur refers to as "Reds"), sometimes both writing on the same day. Majority of entries are in Helen's hand.
They note which artworks they are working on, including specifics of paint and painting techniques used, weather, letters received (including many from Alfred Stieglitz), errands, chores, their health, and social engagements.
Arthur and Helen Torr Dove papers
Archives of American Art, Smithsonian Institution
